I had an experience not entirely unlike the French restaurant. After high school me and my best friend traveled around Europe for a couple months, something we'd been planning and saving for for years, and I was the designated "German" guy because I'd taken a couple years. Anyway, we were in Austria at a restaurant and I was supposed to order for us when I realized that A. people speak a lot faster when actually conversing in a language than they do in a class and B. once you learn the grammar and whatnot for a language, the main barrier to understanding a conversation is knowing words well enough that you can follow a thread when someone is talking quickly, because there are things like tense and gender, plurals, etc. that sound just different enough that you don't instantly make the connection to the root word. Anyhow, we wanted steaks and we got them, sort of. Technically what I ordered was the "Hunter's Platter" that was this absurd dish for a table that contained like 4 steaks, a dozen sausages, and like 3 other types of meat. The plate must have weighed 25 lbs. Fortunately it was just a couple of friends and not a date, so could laugh about it and pack like 10lb of meat each in to-go bags for meals for the next few days. My friend also wanted a salad, so we ordered that and what we got was a "meat salad" which was rolled slices of ham with cream cheese filling. Needless to say we were both laughing pretty hard by that point, and fortunately for us we walked everywhere, so we actually managed to burn a lot of those calories.
